<img width="1062" height="598" class="wp-image-1622077" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/FRSC.jpg" alt="FRSC" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/FRSC.jpg?width=1062&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1062w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/FRSC-300x169.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/FRSC-1024x577.jpg?width=1024&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1024w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/FRSC-768x432.jpg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1062px) 100vw, 1062px" /> By Fortune EromoseleThe Acting Corps Marshal of the Federal Road Safety Corps, FRSC, Dauda Ali Biu, has charged Commanding Officers across board to caution operatives under their purview against extortion, patrol misconduct and unprofessional behaviour in the discharge of their duties. The charge came during his inaugural virtual meeting with the Zonal Commanding Officers of the Corps. Biu directed the commanding officers to increase monitoring and supervision of operatives, improve surveillance on all operational fronts and more importantly, engage Staff continually for sustained value reorientation. He also directed the 12 Zonal Commanding Officers to with immediate effect visit component commands under their jurisdictions of influence, assess their immediate needs and challenges and forward reports of such visits to the national headquarters for urgent intervention. He cautioned against all forms of extortion, bribery and corruption and any kind of misconduct by patrol men stating that the FRSC management will not tolerate incivility towards members of the public, as well as any unprofessional conduct that will bring disrepute to the image of the Corps. While speaking on the need for more visibility, he emphasised that field operations must be intelligence driven, and personnel must be aware and understand the peculiar challenges within their general operation areas and adjust operational activities to boost intelligence gathering. To this end, Biu directed the immediate reawakening of field operations for greater productivity putting into consideration, the expectations of Nigerians especially the motoring public on the Corps delivery on its mandate.    2022 Sallah: FRSC deploys 36,000 officers, 750 patrol vans, others to avert crashes, gridlock In "News" Buhari appoints Biu as Acting FRSC Corps Marshal In "News" The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Ogun Command, on Sunday said that a passerby died in a multiple accident that involved three vehicles at Toll-Gate on Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway In "Metro"